column5: Hi I'm throwing this out there to anyone in the Cache Bay, Sturgeon Falls area.  I'm asking if the Lake water levels have receded enough to make the docks in Cache Bay and Lavigne fishable/safe? Thanks, Mike
I don't think so, the level is crazy high everywhere, West Nippissing closed their public launches the other day. Nippissing is going up 1 cm every day apparently. Hope this helps..
Thanks.  Will take a mulligan this weekend I think.  Season opener this Saturday on Nipissing right?  Have a safe long weekend.  Mike
